07/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Hari Kostov and the ministers of local self-government and finance, Aleksander Gestakovski and Nikola Popovski, met with the ruling coalition parties on Sunday (6 June) to discuss the new territorial division and fiscal decentralisation laws. 
They discussed a proposal to establish ten more municipalities, in addition to the initially proposed 62.
In other news, local security experts attending a seminar Friday agreed that poverty and unemployment are the main reasons for instability in Macedonia. 
They also concluded that ethnic integration and accession to NATO and the EU are the only ways for the country to prevent new conflicts. 
(A1 TV, Makfax - 06/06/04; A1 TV - 04/06/04)
